# PrestaShop module authoring

- **Do not modify core.** Extend via hooks, Symfony services, and module code only.
- **Module structure:** One main class file (e.g. `ps_webp.php`), and a `config.xml` with `<name>`, `<displayName>`, `<description>`, `<version>`, `<author>`, `<is_configurable>`, `<need_instance>`. Keep `displayName` and `description` in sync with the class `$this->displayName` / `$this->description` (use `$this->trans('...', [], 'Modules.Modulename.Admin')` in the class).
- **Author:** Always set `$this->author = 'Rafal Majdan';` in the module class and `<author><![CDATA[Rafal Majdan]]></author>` in `config.xml`. Do not use a different author name.
- **Logo:** Every created module must include a `logo.png` image in the module root (used in the module list in BO). Copy it from `prestashop/modules/tc_stickybar/logo.png`.
- **After creating a new module:** Run `make perms-cache` in the project root terminal so the container (www-data) has write access to `prestashop/modules` and related paths; required for config, uploads, and cache.
- **Security:** Add an `index.php` in each folder that only contains headers and `exit;` so directories are not listable (see `prestashop/modules/ps_webp/index.php` and `config/index.php`).
- **Configurable modules:** Use `HelperForm` for the config form, `Configuration::get()` / `Configuration::updateValue()` for settings, and a dedicated key prefix (e.g. `PS_WEBP_*`). On save, persist any data needed by standalone scripts (e.g. JSON in `config/`) if the script does not bootstrap PrestaShop.
- **Hooks:** Register only the hooks you use; implement the corresponding `hookDisplay*` / `hookAction*` methods. Prefer existing hooks over overrides.
- **Front-office display (widgets):** If the module renders content on display hooks (e.g. `displayHome`, `displayLeftColumn`), implement `PrestaShop\PrestaShop\Core\Module\WidgetInterface`: add `renderWidget($hookName, array $configuration)` (return HTML from template) and `getWidgetVariables($hookName, array $configuration)` (return array for template). Use the logical path `module:modulename/template_name.tpl` (file lives under `views/templates/hook/` or module root). See e.g. `ps_banner`, `ps_featuredproducts`.
- **Partials and reusable components (global, in theme):** All partials and reusable UI components (e.g. product-tile, button) must be **global** and stored in the **theme**, not in modules. Create them under `prestashop/themes/<theme>/templates/_partials/` (e.g. `_partials/product-tile.tpl`, `_partials/button.tpl`). Modules must **not** ship their own `views/templates/_partials/` for FO; instead they include theme partials via `{include file='_partials/name.tpl' ...}` and pass variables from `getWidgetVariables()`. This keeps one source of truth in the theme and allows reuse across modules and pages.
- **Buttons (CTA / link as button):** Never write a button or link-styled-as-button by hand in a template. Always use the theme component `_partials/button.tpl`. Example: `{include file='_partials/button.tpl' url=$button_url label=$button_text btn_class='tc-mymodule__button' target=$button_new_tab}`. See `prestashop/themes/meblowosk/templates/_partials/product-slider.tpl` for usage. Parameters: `url`, `label`, `btn_class` (optional), `target` (truthy = open in new tab), `icon_type` (e.g. `'arrow-right'`, `'arrow-left'`, `'none'`).
- **Translations:** Use the domain `Modules.<TechnicalName>.Admin` (e.g. `Modules.Ps_webp.Admin`) for back-office strings. Optional: add `translations/index.php` that redirects to parent for security.
- **Version:** Set `$this->ps_versions_compliancy` (e.g. `['min' => '1.7.7.0', 'max' => _PS_VERSION_]`) and match version in `config.xml`.
- **Module list shows technical name / "invalid":** If the main class file has a **PHP parse error** (e.g. duplicate or incomplete method, method declared inside another method), PrestaShop cannot load the module: the "Other" list shows only the technical name (e.g. `ps_webp`) with empty author/version/description, and installation fails with "Moduł jest nieprawidłowy" (module invalid). Fix: run `php -l prestashop/modules/<name>/<name>.php` to find the syntax error and correct it; then the display name and install will work.

