## Front-office CSS and JavaScript (must live in _dev)

- **All frontend CSS and JS for modules must be written in `_dev/`**, not in the module’s `views/` directory. Do not put FO styles or scripts in `modules/<name>/views/css/` or `views/js/`, and do not register them via `registerJavascript()` / `registerStylesheet()` from the module.
- **SCSS:** Add section styles in `_dev/css/custom/sections/` (e.g. `_banner-tabs.scss`) and forward them in `_dev/css/custom/sections/_index.scss`. The theme build compiles them into the theme assets.
- **JavaScript:** Add section scripts in `_dev/js/custom/Sections/` (e.g. `BannerTabs.js`). Import and run the initialiser from `_dev/js/custom/theme.js` (e.g. `import initBannerTabs from './Sections/BannerTabs'; runWhenReady(initBannerTabs);`). The theme build bundles them; the module only renders the HTML (e.g. via `views/templates/hook/`).

