## Image input in a repeater (list of items with icon/photo)

- **Form:** Use **HelperForm** with `'type' => 'file'`, `'name' => 'icon'` (or another name). HelperForm sets `enctype="multipart/form-data"` automatically. Do **not** set `override_folder` on the helper — then the template loads from `modules/<name>/views/templates/admin/_configure/helpers/form/form.tpl`.
- **Image preview in BO:** The default form template outputs the `image` value (URL) as plain text. To show an actual **image** (`<img>`):
  1. Add a template override: `views/templates/admin/_configure/helpers/form/form.tpl` extending `helpers/form/form.tpl`.
  2. In `{block name="field"}` handle `$input.type == 'file' && $input.name == 'icon'`: output `<img src="{$icon_preview_url}" class="img-thumbnail" />` when preview exists, then the `type="file"` input and an “Add file” button.
  3. In PHP: pass the **full URL** for the preview in `$helper->tpl_vars['icon_preview_url']` (e.g. `rtrim($this->context->link->getBaseLink(), '/') . '/' . ltrim($this->_path, '/') . 'views/img/icons/' . $item->icon`). On save: `move_uploaded_file()` to a directory in the module (e.g. `views/img/icons/`) and store the filename in the entity/configuration.
- **Reference modules:** `ps_iconbar` and `tc_stickybar` — repeater with icon, HelperForm + custom `form.tpl` for preview; `ps_banner` — single image with `type => 'file_lang'` and custom template.

