## File permissions and image input

- **Common cause of issues:** When saving/uploading an image in a module fails, the cause is **often write permissions** on directories (BO shows “Set write permissions for folder modules / cache / img…”).
- **Fix:** On the host (project root) run: `make perms` (file ownership), then **`make perms-cache`** — it sets write access for `prestashop/modules`, `prestashop/config`, `prestashop/img`, `prestashop/var/cache`, `prestashop/translations`, `prestashop/upload`, `prestashop/download`, `prestashop/mails`, `prestashop/app/config`, `prestashop/app/Resources/translations`, so the container (www-data) can write there.
- **After `make cache-clear`:** If the permissions error reappears in BO, run `make perms-cache` again.
